  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-22 07:45 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] 07h Is Not Decay, It Is Mid-Conviction Persistence Inside the Same Pinned Regime\n\n**Task:** Compare 07h against the confirmed 06h regime to see whether the next excluded hour shows meaningful decay or simply a different conviction mix inside the same state.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains out of active hours.\n- **06h** and **07h** are structurally identical so far:\n  - both are entirely pinned in `(0.505, 0.495)`\n- But their conviction profiles differ:\n  - **06h:**\n    - **59** windows\n    - `|bias| >= 45` in **25** windows (**42.4%**)\n    - `|bias| >= 55` in **15** windows (**25.4%**)\n  - **07h:**\n    - **45** windows\n    - `|bias| >= 45` in **24** windows (**53.3%**)\n    - `|bias| >= 55` in **7** windows (**15.6%**)\n- So 07h is **not** a clean decay phase. It has more mid-strength conviction but fewer high-conviction spikes.\n- Wrote new research artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v7o-post-confirmation-decay.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThe useful insight is not \u201c07h got weaker.\u201d It\u2019s more nuanced. The market stayed pinned in the same regime, but the conviction distribution compressed toward the middle. That means 07h is persistent, but not especially explosive. It continues the same excluded structure without creating a better case for live inclusion.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep **07h excluded**.\n- Classify 07h as **mid-conviction persistence**, not as a new candidate hour.\n- Preserve the rule that stable excluded hours are not enough, especially when they fail to generate stronger high-conviction structure than the prior confirmation hour.\n\n**Next:** On the next P2 heartbeat, compare 07h against the active-hour profile to quantify how much worse its high-conviction density is than live trading windows, not just other excluded hours.\n\n---\n## 2026-04